Package pkgMain

  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    AddPlantListScreen
    The PlantListScreen class is a screen that lists the plants in the garden.
    Controller
    The controller class for the native garden designer application.
    CreateNewGardenScreen
    The CreateNewGardenScreen represent the screen where the user can edit and create a garden.
    EditorScreen
    The EditorScreen class is a screen where the user can edit parts of the garden.
    EditPreexistingGardenScreen
    The EditPreexisitingGardenScreen displays a screen on which plants can be dragged onto the garden
    Garden
    The Garden class represents a garden with different conditions and can have plants placed and moved around in it.
    GardenPlant
    The GardenPlant class represents a plant placed in the garden, having a location and associated plant.
    GenInfoScreen
    The GenInfoScreen shows some general information about why native plants are important in gardens
    Lep
    The Lep class represents a lep, lepidoptera, that can be supported by a plant.
    LepImage
    The LepImage class represents a lep with its image, genus, and species
    LepListScreen
    The LepListScreen class is a screen that lists the leps in the garden.
    LoadGardenScreen
    The LoadGardenScreen allows the user to load a previously saved garden.
    MainScreen
    MainScreen displays the scene that shows the garden and allows the user to see many aspects of the garden, as well as access many different screens.
    Model
    The model class is the model of the program, allowing creation and interaction with a garden.
    Plant
    The plant class represents a plant that can support different leps and grow in different conditions.
    PlantImage
    The PlantImage class represents a plant with its image, genus, and species
    PlantListScreen
    The screen that is responsible for displaying all the plants in a tableview.
    PlantMoreInfoScreen
    The screen that is responsible for displaying the informations for a plant.
    Screen
    The abstract class Screen defines values that all screens need to have and methods
    StartScreen  
    Toast
    The class for toast message (android style popup message).
    View
    The View class shows different screens to the user.
